Package hippodrome.responses

Provides the classes necessary to answer and represent any response from a entity state change, in order to well update the current state of a given thread's execution.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Response
    Class that provides the needed marshalling options to enable the correct return values for each entity's state changes and actual return values.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ResponseType
    Class that provides the encoding to the various type of responses.

Package hippodrome.responses Description

Provides the classes necessary to answer and represent any response from a entity state change, in order to well update the current state of a given thread's execution. Its contents are a Response and a ResponseType.
Since:
2.0
See Also:
hippodrome, server, entities
